New Bayern Munich signing Robert Lewandowski gave a glimpse of things to come with a superb improvised finish in a pre season friendly against Borussia Monchengladbach.

The Polish centre forward arrived this summer on a free transfer from Bundesliga rivals Borussia Dortmund - and he already has two pre season goals since his arrival.

The second of those came on Sunday with a chip over the outcoming goalkeeper used as a way to get past his four markers in the box.

