And while Bayern drew 2-2 before eventually winning on penalties, it was a happy occasion all round with Franck Ribery making his return to the side after the back injury which ruled him out of the World Cup.

And with Lewandowski looking like the perfect line leader for Pep Guardiola's side, the German champions could again have their opponents quaking in their boots at home and abroad.

